                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 12.797,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 79872,
                                "text": "The judgment and opinion of the Court in Number 1323, Norfolk and Western Railway Company against Liepelt will be announced by Mr. Justice Stevens."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 12.797,
                        "stop": 124.091,
                        "byte_start": 79872,
                        "byte_stop": 525103,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15060,
                            "name": "John Paul Stevens",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/john_paul_stevens",
                            "last_name": "Stevens",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2704,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 188200800,
                                    "date_end": 1277787600,
                                    "appointing_president": "Gerald Ford",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2704"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32732,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 62101,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/john_paul_stevens.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 12611,
                            "identifier": "john_paul_stevens"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 12.797,
                                "stop": 20.604,
                                "byte_start": 79872,
                                "byte_stop": 111114,
                                "text": "In 1973, a fireman employed by the Norfolk and Western Railway suffered fatal injuries in a collision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.604,
                                "stop": 32.225,
                                "byte_start": 111114,
                                "byte_stop": 157612,
                                "text": "His widow brought suit in the Circuit Court of Cook County, Illinois against the Railroad under the Federal Employer\u0027s Liability Act and recovered damages of $775,000."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 32.225,
                                "stop": 43.201,
                                "byte_start": 157612,
                                "byte_stop": 201498,
                                "text": "An appeal to the Appellate Court of Illinois, the Railroad argued that the jury may have overestimated the monetary law suffered by the fireman\u0027s survivors for two reasons."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 43.201,
                                "stop": 58.351,
                                "byte_start": 201498,
                                "byte_stop": 262102,
                                "text": "First, when the plaintiff\u0027s expert testified, his calculations were based on the decendents before tax earnings and the judge would not allow the Railroad\u0027s lawyer to offer any evidence concerning the amount of income taxes paid by the employee."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.351,
                                "stop": 65.149,
                                "byte_start": 262102,
                                "byte_stop": 289270,
                                "text": "Second, the judge refused to instruct the jury that the plaintiff\u0027s recovery would not be subject to federal income taxes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 65.149,
                                "stop": 81.898,
                                "byte_start": 289270,
                                "byte_stop": 356352,
                                "text": "The Illinois Appellate Court affirmed the trial judge because his rulings were consistent with the prevailing practice of refusing to allow juries to receive evidence or instruction concerning the impact of federal income taxes on damage awards in cases under the statute."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 81.898,
                                "stop": 92.913,
                                "byte_start": 356352,
                                "byte_stop": 400342,
                                "text": "Because the prevailing practice developed at a time when federal taxes were relatively insignificant and because some courts are now following a different practice, we granted certiorari."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.913,
                                "stop": 110.381,
                                "byte_start": 400342,
                                "byte_stop": 470246,
                                "text": "We now reverse and hold that the wage earner\u0027s federal income taxes are one of the factors relevant in measuring the monetary law as occasioned by his death and further, that it was error to refuse to instruct the jury that no taxes would be -- would be assessed against this recovery."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 110.381,
                                "stop": 118.43,
                                "byte_start": 470246,
                                "byte_stop": 502429,
                                "text": "Accordingly, for reasons stated in an opinion filed with the clerk, the case is remanded to the Appellate Court of Illinois for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 118.43,
                                "stop": 124.091,
                                "byte_start": 502429,
                                "byte_stop": 525103,
                                "text": "Mr. Justice Blackmun with whom Mr. Justice Marshall joins has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
